  <h1 class="about-subheading">Education</h1>

  <p>
    In 2009, he enrolled at the Vito Volterra <strong>Scientific High
    School</strong> (Fabriano), graduating in <strong>2014</strong>. His high
    school years left a lasting mark on him, for better or for worse. He took
    part in numerous extracurricular projects, including theatre, where he
    played the role of Siro in the Machiavelli’s
    <a href="https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mandragola_(commedia)">Mandragola</a>.
    His marry theatre mates remain trusted fella in his adventures even in
    later life.
  </p>

  <p>
    Being undecided between studying a science or a humanities subject, he
    felt that agriculture might be the right combination of the two and the
    right compromise given what the educational environment and economic
    situation offered at the time.
  </p>

  <p>
    In 2014, he enrolled at the Faculty of
    <a href="https://www.univpm.it/Entra/"><strong>Agricultural Sciences and
    Technologies</strong></a> in Ancona, obtaining a <strong>B.Sc.</strong>
    in <strong>2018</strong> with a thesis on the historiography of
    intercropping and crop rotation, having been captivated by the
    ‘Alternative Crops’ course at the
    <a href="https://www.czu.cz/en"><strong>Czech University of Life
    Science</strong></a> (2016–2017).
  </p>

  <p>
    In <strong>2020</strong>, he obtained a <strong>M.Sc.</strong> in
    <strong>Sustainable Agriculture</strong> from the
    <a href="https://apply.unipd.it/courses/course/19-sustainable-agriculture"><strong>University
    of Padua</strong></a>, writing a meta-analysis on the variation of
    functional traits in cocoa plants between agroforestry systems and
    monoculture plantations, carried out at the <strong>University of
    Göttingen</strong> at
    <a href="https://www.uni-goettingen.de/en/106511.html">TROPAGS lab</a>
    (2019–2020).
  </p>

  <p>
    In <strong>2026</strong>, he obtained a <strong>PhD</strong> in
    <strong>Agricultural Science</strong> from
    <a href="https://sae.ethz.ch"><strong>ETH Zurich</strong></a>, with a
    dissertation titled:
    <a href="https://www.research-collection.ethz.ch/server/api/core/bitstreams/26138243-9461-416b-9ceb-896eab63953d/content">“Agricultural
    diversification through the use of underutilised crops”</a>.
  </p>
